# AI Agent Development Rules - MANDATORY COMPLIANCE ## PRE-WORK REQUIREMENTS 1. ALWAYS read package.json before importing any library 2. ALWAYS check if test framework is installed before writing tests 3. NEVER assume APIs exist - read the implementation file first 4. ALWAYS understand existing code patterns before modifying ## TESTING MANDATES 1. EVERY new component MUST have corresponding test file 2. EVERY new utility function MUST have unit tests 3. EVERY API route modification MUST include integration tests 4. ALL tests must pass (`npm test`) before task completion 5. Test coverage must not drop below current baseline ## CODE INTEGRITY RULES 1. NEVER import libraries not in package.json without explicit permission 2. ALWAYS follow existing code patterns and conventions 3. NEVER modify database schema without migration planning 4. ALWAYS run type checking (`npm run build`) before finishing 5. PRESERVE existing functionality - no regressions allowed ## VERIFICATION CHECKLIST - [ ] npm run build (type check) - [ ] npm run lint (code quality) - [ ] npm test (all tests pass) - [ ] No new console errors in browser - [ ] Existing functionality preserved - [ ] Branch pushed to remote for PR creation